                        >Tabṣirat al-Maẕāhib va Taẕkirat al-Adyān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">دبستان</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">تبصرت
                        المذاهب و تذکرت الادیان</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">Dabistān
                        al-Maẕāhib</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup"
                        >Dabistān-i Maẕāhib</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmalla"><locus from="1a" to="1a"> برگ ۱ر (folio
                           1a):</locus> ای نام تو سر دفتر اطفال دبستان * یاد ببالغ نظران شمع
                        شبستان.</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="286a" to="286a"> برگ ٢٨۶ر (folio
                           286a):</locus> غرض نقشی‌ست کز ما ياد ماند * که هستی را نمی بینم بقائی. </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa"><locus from="286a" to="286a"> برگ ٢٨۶ر (folio
                           286a):</locus> تم تم تمام شد صورت اختسام یافت. نسخه دبستان مذاهب بخط بنده
                        کاشی ناتهہ قوم بر همن متوطن ملک پنجاب بلده سیالکوت تحریر پذیرفت پانزدهم شهر
                        رمضان المبارک سنهتم. ۱۲۱۰ هجری .</colophon>
                     <colophon> Completed by <persName key="person_f1839" role="scr"
                           change="#role-assignment">Kāshī Nath</persName>, a Hindu Brahmin from
                           <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/1083799"
                           key="place_1083799">Sialkot, Punjab</placeName>, on <date
                           calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1796-03-24">15 Ramaz̤ān 1210 AH (24 Mar.
                           1796 CE)</date>. </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>A note on the margins of folio:<lb/><q xml:lang="fa">محسن فانی
                           گوید...</q><lb/> (<q xml:lang="en">Muḥsin Fānī says...</q>) refers to
                        authorship of those verses, not the entire work. Former owner <persName
                           key="person_f2018" role="ins aut fmo" change="#role-assignment">Samuel
                           Hawtayne Lewin</persName>, cites an addendum by Sir W. Ouseley
                           (<title>Travels</title>, Vol. III, p. 564) who attributes the work to
                           <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Mūbad Shāh</persName> and
                        identifies Muhsin Fani as only the <q xml:lang="en">poet quoted at the
                           beginning</q>, on the basis of this manuscript, then in the possession of
                        former owner <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/19247044/"
                           key="person_19247044" role="fmo ins"
                           change="#role-assignment #ids-cleanup">Jonathan Duncan</persName>, a
                        position accepted by current scholars. For another illustrated copy of this
                        work also formerly owned by Duncan, see Rylands <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7254"><idno>Persian
                              MS 75</idno></ref> and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6671"
                              ><idno>190</idno></ref>. Regarding the attribution of authorship for
                        this work to <persName key="person_f3013" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" role="aut"
                           >Mīr Ẕū al-Fiqār ‘Alī al-Ḥusaynī Ardistānī</persName>, see Mojtabāʾī and
                        Barzegar.</note>
                  </msItem>
